headline: How DEI Investing Has Changed Under Trump
summary: While companies such as Target have blamed DEI backlash for lower sales, others, such as Costco, are seeing boosts to foot traffic. So how can companies' DEI commitments affect investors with a socially conscious approach to investing? In this bonus episode of WSJ’s Take On the Week, we are joined by Rachel Robasciotti, founder of investment firm Adasina Social Capital.
